Welcome to August's Turing-Roche newsletter! Here you can find what's new in the Turing-Roche strategic partnership and opportunities, events and news from both The Alan Turing Institute and Roche.

Our [five year partnership](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2Fd5hgCr0ho689ioprRcuuxA&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Ce7377f2dfdb944c6017008da794f9f09%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637955680134679468%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=qQwQay0%2BwsEVE3aW2bLJiGhoSV9C3kB1MCn0M%2Fe5Egc%3D&reserved=0) was set up officially in June 2021 following a successful [Data Study Group](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2F0GEfGku913Huvs3kE7nPmQ&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Ce7377f2dfdb944c6017008da794f9f09%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637955680134835685%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=o1SimZ8SxNLOtGQGHXe475LTKt5TIIukyuLPITYUbII%3D&reserved=0) and a 12 week research project on lung cancer treatment. Our 'North Star' is **to enable the generation of insights to better understand patient and disease heterogeneity and its relevance to clinical outcomes at an unprecedented level of precision in order to improve clinical care. **

We will be covering multiple activities over the five years to work towards our North Star, as well as building strong connections and collaborations between the Alan Turing Institute, Roche and the wider community.

If you have anything you'd like featured in a future newsletter then please get in touch with Vicky Hellon, Community Manager for the partnership at <vhellon@turing.ac.uk>

If you would like to share this newsletter with relevant colleagues please direct them to sign-up [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FgZHNHqM67bfIY7YqMc0fdA&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Ce7377f2dfdb944c6017008da794f9f09%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637955680134835685%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=NIqLOBZRibeZMScWg1SYgtPX10b7kNUll1kHwjIC3dE%3D&reserved=0).

## **Turing-Roche Strategic Partnership Updates**

![](https://file-eu.clickdimensions.com/turingacuk-ap7zg/files/photo-1457530378978-8bac673b8062.jfif)

### **First funded projects to start in September**

We're excited to formally announce our first research projects as a partnership! We have awarded funding for two 18-month projects in the area of Structured Missingness to Professor Ginestra Bianconi and Dr Robin Mitra and their teams. The competitive funding call ran earlier this year after [3 collaborative workshops](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FDqS7ebSi8iFzW107TWE_Dg&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Ce7377f2dfdb944c6017008da794f9f09%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637955680134835685%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=GSwL3nCYd%2FDxa5odGcozPItf2KdeDuXWhRaAM1sDLpU%3D&reserved=0) which convened a group of researchers to discuss and scope out approaches to structural missing data.

The projects will be starting in September and taking a collaborative approach. They will be sharing regular updates through our [Slack Workspace](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2F8FSc9BM5VnzxDM7KUuSVAg&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Ce7377f2dfdb944c6017008da794f9f09%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637955680134835685%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=K10L0pz15Te1bOte4Rsun3iJOJID4V%2FtMXr%2F%2FBA1wi4%3D&reserved=0) and [Knowledge Share events](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FBMR3S0WNvHykusN1vEHtUw&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Ce7377f2dfdb944c6017008da794f9f09%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637955680134835685%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=O3IofI8hKzPMYidwdLnMVUPh66sk3obfF7yo3lgksSY%3D&reserved=0), as well as open publications of methods, algorithms and results.

You can find out more about the projects [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FwaadYnheiLk3DD1BkM45pQ&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Ce7377f2dfdb944c6017008da794f9f09%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637955680134835685%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=C8CV8hGBiDidRRKmtL1%2BXUMhAb%2BX2OQEGhIcWFysbpg%3D&reserved=0).

### **Become a Turing Data Study Group Principal Investigator**

The Turing Data Study Groups (DSG) are collaborative hackathons which bring together organisations from industry, government, and the third sector, with talented multi-disciplinary researchers from academia. (The Turing-Roche Partnership started with a DSG). Each DSG has a Principal Investigator (PI) who liases with the challenge owner, facilitates the research direction of the overall project and helps to put together the final report.

The Turing is now recruiting early career researchers to take on this role allowing them to acquire project management skills, fine tune their ability to convert commercial ideas into research projects and experience how research projects can generate real world impact. More information and how to apply [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%_X2NsZGVlPXFsOHp0S2xBU3ZDODN0alpDeE9JcHhESGtSMnd6dUpmc1ZBbVZiMHdOV0s5bzVSMWNNRTN6UjEtR0VDcVBudFAmcmVjaXBpZW50aWQ9Y29udGFjdC00ODgwYThjMzkyM2NlYzExOGM2MjAwMjI0ODQzNGZlYi0xNDE1ZTRlZGJmNDE0ZmMzODJhNDRiNWIxZjZhMmQyZSZlc2lkPTRjMDA0NDU0LTJjMTMtZWQxMS1iODNlLTAwMGQzYWQ1ODZmMyJ9%2FX54VfBOBkoHokvo_uuspOA&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Ce7377f2dfdb944c6017008da794f9f09%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637955680134991901%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=jsK%2FbQ%2FKZgteo7tQwPnjUV5jpMe%2BNqbiSzpYm59bXEQ%3D&reserved=0).

### **Manchester Digital Epidemiology School 2022**

**12-14 October 2022**

The Centre for Epidemiology Versus Arthritis is hosting the 4th Manchester Digital Epidemiology School. ### **Call to add your tool to the Genomic Data Diversity Initiative**

The Genomic Data Diversity Initiative is a global open source and community driven initiative to improve inequalities in genomic research and medicine. They are at the pre-launch stage and one of the activities they are undertaking is searching and cataloguing tools (i.e any solutions that provide practical help to a person working on improving equity in genomic medicine, such as handbooks or software packages). Find out more on how to contribute at this [twitter thread](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FDazeRYdAxKRaRbXquN6rSw&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Ce7377f2dfdb944c6017008da794f9f09%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637955680135148125%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=5BturCZZc0DxA8ibsbSolgl0%2FV3MAdWeVn7xaJPDJLw%3D&reserved=0).

### **Assessing, visualizing and improving the utility of synthetic data**

September's publication of the month is [this paper](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%_X2NsZGVlPXFsOHp0S2xBU3ZDODN0alpDeE9JcHhESGtSMnd6dUpmc1ZBbVZiMHdOV0s5bzVSMWNNRTN6UjEtR0VDcVBudFAmcmVjaXBpZW50aWQ9Y29udGFjdC00ODgwYThjMzkyM2NlYzExOGM2MjAwMjI0ODQzNGZlYi0xNDE1ZTRlZGJmNDE0ZmMzODJhNDRiNWIxZjZhMmQyZSZlc2lkPTRjMDA0NDU0LTJjMTMtZWQxMS1iODNlLTAwMGQzYWQ1ODZmMyJ9%2FhlOr8Ov12YZWmR5hWbm4gw&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Ce7377f2dfdb944c6017008da794f9f09%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637955680135148125%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=Wd9hbjRldw%2Fc9ZEKO0HKXlLXTRCZakQNR7oS1CwFFys%3D&reserved=0) on the R package synthpop which provides tools to allow data custodians to create synthetic versions of microdata and reproduce the relationships in real data in the synthetic data. This paper is written by Professor Gillian Raab and colleagues and was kindly shared as a resource in our [Turing-Roche Slack Workspace](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2Fkjc_RD7xQtJb5aXfOUHZGg&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Ce7377f2dfdb944c6017008da794f9f09%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637955680135148125%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=npu2k38yZnNqHEz1ghqVU6gLwMA17CoCgN%2BQtGrx8kU%3D&reserved=0) following our recent Synthetic Data Knowledge Share [event](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%_dj1ZSm5SRXpjU2s5YyZfY2xkZWU9cWw4enRLbEFTdkM4M3RqWkN4T0lweERIa1Iyd3p1SmZzVkFtVmIwd05XSzlvNVIxY01FM3pSMS1HRUNxUG50UCZyZWNpcGllbnRpZD1jb250YWN0LTQ4ODBhOGMzOTIzY2VjMTE4YzYyMDAyMjQ4NDM0ZmViLTE0MTVlNGVkYmY0MTRmYzM4MmE0NGI1YjFmNmEyZDJlJmVzaWQ9NGMwMDQ0NTQtMmMxMy1lZDExLWI4M2UtMDAwZDNhZDU4NmYzIn0%2FE5ZB2s9j3NMljFCLw9ELcA&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Ce7377f2dfdb944c6017008da794f9f09%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637955680135148125%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=ojQqEzjblIAhPPmpE23igChXhRAB%2FKwnMUBOA%2B6nVHc%3D&reserved=0).
